ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 1
 show images of the CQDs as-exfoliated in solution of sodium nitrate, including TEM image (a), HRTEM image (b), and size distribution histogram and its fitted Gaussian curve (c). As shown in Fig. 1(a), most of the CQDs are torispherical in shape and uniformly distribution without aggregation. As revealed in the HRTEM image, the distinct lattice spacing of CQDs are about 0.21 nm, corresponding to the (100) lattice plane of graphite [29,30]. The size distribution histogram of the CQDs and its fitting Gaussian curve are shown in Fig. 1 (c), which base on statistical analysis of more than 200 CQDs obtained from one or more TEM images, and the average size of CQDs is size position of the fitting Gaussian peak. The sizes of CQDs distribute in range of 1.1–5.5 nm and the average size is 3.15 nm, both which are larger than the CQDs exfoliated in other inorganic electrolytes (as show in Fig. 2
).
